# Process the stock data
import numpy as np

# Calculate moving averages
data['MA20'] = data['Close'].rolling(window=20).mean()
data['MA50'] = data['Close'].rolling(window=50).mean()

# Calculate daily returns
data['Returns'] = data['Close'].pct_change() * 100

# Drop NaN values
data_clean = data.dropna()

print(f"Processed data shape: {data_clean.shape}")
data_clean.head()

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

fig = plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
plt.plot(data_clean.index, data_clean['Close'], label='Close Price')
plt.plot(data_clean.index, data_clean['MA20'], label='20-day MA', linestyle='--')
plt.plot(data_clean.index, data_clean['MA50'], label='50-day MA', linestyle='-.')

plt.title(f'{ticker} Stock Price (2023)')
plt.xlabel('Date')
plt.ylabel('Price ($)')
plt.legend()
plt.grid(True, alpha=0.6)
